<item>
            <title>[LU-17814] &quot;lfs find&quot; to scan with multiple threads</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17814</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful for &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to perform directory scans with multiple threads in parallel.  It could (potentially) fork a new thread (or put a work item into a pool) for each subdirectory so that they can be scanned in parallel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is &quot;libcircle&quot; and &quot;libpcircle&quot; that can perform workload sharing to speed up directory traversal.  Also, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/VI4IO/pfind.git&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;pfind&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; code in IO500 is also doing efficient parallel directory traversal, including splitting up large directories by hash index to traverse in parallel.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Integrating one of these algorithms into &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; with pthreads would allow a many-fold improvement in directory scanning performance.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
